Measuring Success in Ad-Blocker-Resistant Marketing
Measuring marketing effectiveness changes when moving away from paid advertising. Different metrics reveal success in alternative channels.

Email engagement metrics track audience quality. Open rates, click-through rates, unsubscribe rates—these reveal email performance. Strong engagement indicates valuable content and healthy list quality.

Website traffic and search visibility metrics reveal organic success. Traffic growth, keyword ranking improvements, and search visibility improvements measure SEO success. Organic traffic trends reveal strategy effectiveness.

Content performance metrics show what resonates. Page views, time on page, scroll depth, conversions—these metrics reveal content quality and relevance.

Lead generation and conversion metrics measure business impact. Marketing-sourced leads, conversion rates, and cost per acquisition reveal whether marketing generates business results.

Customer acquisition cost (CAC) across channels reveals efficiency. CAC for email-sourced customers versus content-sourced versus referral-sourced reveals which channels drive most efficient customer acquisition.

Customer lifetime value (LTV) reveals customer quality. Customers from different sources often have different retention and expansion revenue potential. LTV analysis guides channel investment.

Share of voice in owned channels measures audience reach. Email list size, website traffic, social followers—these owned audience metrics reveal reach across channels.

Attribution modeling reveals channel contributions. Understanding which channels contribute to conversions guides continued investment. Multi-touch attribution reveals how channels work together.

